pages.transcription:
unkown 5th “89
Dear Mother;
Your postal received saying the money was all right and that you would send it to me in a few days. How strange he should get the name Arnold. I noticed on the Check he had it Arnold with the ld crossed out. Mrs. Ford is holding the lot for you. We are going to two of her. We have one now have paid $40.00 on it and she will pay the other for us. The one we got of Edwards is all paid for but $50.00 and if Dan has more all winter we will get that paid. A man wanted to buy the one we bought of Edwards last night and we wouldn’t let him have it
